(PASTEMAGAZINE) — Monday night, Bernie Sanders did a town hall on CNN, and for the most part, he was asked substantive questions and answered in kind.

One minor exception came in a question about the sexual harassment that took place in his 2016 campaign. His response to the initial reports was too dismissive, and last night he wasn’t able to fully articulate how he would stop it from happening again, other than saying that his campaign is committing lots of resources and he will have the “strongest protocols” and utilize an “independent commission” that people can bring their complaints to, without really elaborating on who or what that commission would do.

